Activity 1: Record-Triggered Flow – High Priority Student Application Notification
Objective: Automatically notify the Enrollment Owner (Counselor) when a student application is identified as high priority by AI. 
Trigger Condition: AI_Priority_Score__c ≥ 80 
Steps: 
1. From Setup, in the Quick Find box, search for Flows.
2. Click New Flow.
3. Select Category: Triggered.
    Select Type: Record-Triggered Flow.
    Select Object: Student_Enrollment__c.
    Configure Trigger: When a record is created or updated.
4. Set Entry Conditions:
    Field: AI_Priority_Score__c
    Operator: Greater than or Equal
    Value: 80
5. Select Run Every time a record is created and meets the condition requirements.
6. Optimize the flow for Actions and Related Records.
7. Click on the + icon and add Send Email Alert action.
8. Select Email Alert: High Priority Student Application Email Alert.
9. Enter the Label as: High Priority Student Application Notification.
10. Map RecordId to the Record Id field.
11. Save the Flow and Activate.


Activity 2: Record-Triggered Flow – High Discount Enrollment Submission for Approval
Objective: Automatically submit a student enrollment for approval when a high discount is applied. 
Trigger Condition: Discount__c > 30
Steps:
1. From Setup, in the Quick Find box, search for Flows.
2. Click New Flow.
3. Select Category: Triggered.
4. Select Type: Record-Triggered Flow.
5. Select Object: Student_Enrollment__c.
6. Configure Trigger: When a record is created or updated.
7. Set Entry Conditions:
    Field: Discount__c
    Operator: Greater than
    Value: 30
8. Select Run Every time a record is created and meets the condition requirements.
9. Optimize the flow for Actions and Related Records.
10.Click on the + icon and add Submit for Approval action.
11.Select Approval Process: High Discount Student Enrollment Approval.
12.Enter the Label as: Submit Enrollment for Approval.
13.Map RecordId to the Record Id field.
14.Save the Flow and Activate.
